  "prompt": "What are the questions asked in interviews?",
  "response": "Interview questions can vary widely depending on the position, industry, and company culture. However, here are some commonly asked questions across many job interviews:\n\n### General Questions\n1. **Tell me about yourself.**\n2. **Why do you want to work here?**\n3. **What do you know about our company?**\n4. **Why did you leave your last job?**\n5. **What is your greatest strength?**\n6. **What is your greatest weakness?**\n7. **Where do you see yourself in 5 years?**\n8. **Why should we hire you?**\n9. **Describe a time when you faced a difficult situation at work and how you handled it.**\n10. **What are your salary expectations?**\n\n### Behavioral Questions\n1. **Give me an example of a time when you worked as part of a team.**\n2. **Tell me about a time when you had to manage multiple tasks.**\n3. **Describe a situation where you had to use problem-solving skills.**\n4. **Can you give me an example of a time when you showed leadership?**\n5. **Tell me about a specific project you worked on and how you managed it.**\n6. **Describe a time when you had to deal with a difficult coworker or client.**\n\n### Technical/Skill-Specific Questions\n1. **What technical skills do you excel at?**\n2. **Can you describe your experience with [specific software or tool]?**\n3. **What techniques do you use to stay updated in your field?**\n4. **Explain a challenging technical problem you solved.**\n5. **Describe your process for debugging and troubleshooting issues.**\n6. **How do you ensure the quality of your work?**\n   \n### Role-Specific Questions\n1. **What experience do you have in [specific tasks related to the job]?**\n2. **How do you prioritize your tasks?**\n3. **What strategies do you use for [specific job-related scenario]?**\n4. **Can you describe a time when you improved a process or system at work?**\n5. **How do you handle deadlines?**\n\n### Cultural Fit Questions\n1. **What kind of work environment do you thrive in?**\n2. **How do you handle stress and pressure?**\n3. **What is your management style?**\n4. **How do you like to be managed?**\n5. **Describe a work culture you did not enjoy and why.**\n\n### Closing Questions\n1. **Do you have any questions for us?**\n2. **Are there any aspects of the role that you would like clarification on?**\n3. **What would be your availability to start?**\n\nRemember, interviews are a two-way street. It's also your opportunity to ask questions and ensure the company and role are the right fit for you.",
